intro: Diplusodon kielmeyeroides, commonly known as the Kielmeyer's rock fig, is a flowering plant native to Australia. It belongs to the family Moraceae and is characterized by its small, clustered leaves and edible fruits. The plant typically grows in rocky or sandy soils and is adapted to arid or semi-arid environments. Its fruits are small, yellowish, and contain a single seed, making it an important species in local ecosystems. It is often found in coastal and inland regions of Queensland and New South Wales.
